      "lineNbr": 74,
      "author": {
        "id": 1174099
      },
      "writtenOn": "2017-11-17T23:39:42Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "\u003e Is there ever an instance where you wouldn\u0027t want to call this instead of Parent_PrepareForCrashingChild? It seems like this API always does the right thing and the former requires more care.\n\nYes. For the things that aren’t gtest death tests, like the use in Multiprocess, the death test style is totally irrelevant. There, we’ll always fork and just run the child straight from the forked side, no intervening execv().\n\nMaybe saying “gtest death test” in the \\brief wasn’t enough to make it clear?",
      "parentUuid": "153da3d6_39ba9d2f",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 74,
        "startChar": 6,
        "endLine": 74,
        "endChar": 58
      },
      "revId": "5ccaad369826eadef3cba8dc8367814712ef4826",
