      "message": "\u003e \u003e \u003e \u003c\u003d ?\n\u003e \u003e \n\u003e \u003e 0 is a valid file descriptor.\n\u003e \n\u003e Sure, but not in this context where STDIN is closed on line 175.\n\nGotcha. I changed this one to |\u003c\u003d STDERR_FILENO|. I left line 175 alone as |\u003c 0|, because it’s only concerned with catching the value if --socket-fd is not specified, and the default value set on line 129 is -1.",
