    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "61f1cd97_a89a82b3",
        "filename": "util/posix/double_fork_and_exec.h",
        "patchSetId": 2
      },
      "lineNbr": 55,
      "author": {
        "id": 1174099
      },
      "writtenOn": "2017-11-17T23:39:42Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "\u003e You could report out failures from the intermediate by controlling the exit status and waitpid, right?\n\nNot really: how long do I wait for in the intermediate? The grandchild’s not supposed to exit at all while DoubleForkAndExec() is running in the parent, but I’ll never know in the intermediate child whether the grandchild has pinched off an execv() or whether it’s just slow.",
      "parentUuid": "38dc1f9d_d4dee84e",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 55,
        "startChar": 8,
        "endLine": 55,
